      "changelog": "## AgentCore v1.1.0\n\n### What's new\n- **Voice improvements:** Kokoro-82M TTS latency reduced from ~1s to ~0.4s on Tier 1 hardware.\n- **RAG precision:** ChromaDB embedding pipeline updated; retrieval accuracy improved ~12%.\n- **Admin dashboard:** New \"System Health\" panel showing CPU/RAM/VRAM usage per agent.\n- **Telegram reliability:** Reconnect loop now handles network drops without requiring restart.\n- **Docker Compose SKU:** License key binding wizard step redesigned — clearer error messages.\n\n### Bug fixes\n- Fixed rare race condition in multi-agent message bus under high load (Profile 6).\n- Fixed STT silence detection cutting off long sentences on slower Tier 1 hardware.\n- Wizard step 7 (model pull) no longer times out on slow connections.\n\n### Security\n- Updated base images to Ubuntu 24.04.2 LTS (patches CVE-2026-1234).\n",
